<div class='commentinfo comment_comment'>
2012-08-03 03:14:53 (666 days ago)
<div id='contact-148574'><span class='name'>Garrick Taylor</span><span class='send-message'><a href="/content/Contact/view/contactid/148574/display/detail/">Details</a></span></div> </div>
<div class='commentbox'>
Ran most of this section this spring. It does still require a permit and you will need your car tag<br/>
info and your driver's license number for the permit. Can take a little while to get it all filled<br/>
out and the run drops out super fast. Super tight little creek run. Lots of wood to be avoided and<br/>
portaged - stop to scout when on your way up. I would recommend at least 3 in the group. Have a<br/>
couple of folks paddle down while 1 is on shore for support. Boat down a short distance and rotate<br/>
spots while the shore support boats on down. We didn't finish due to a pin on some hidden wood in a<br/>
drop. Wasn't a bad situation but it could have been. High quality run that I can't wait to hit<br/>
again with a slightly larger crew. </div>
</td>
</tr>
